value: Breeds in Europe and northern Asia from the Faroes, middle Norway, northern Sweden, Russia north to lat. 62Â° (59Â° in the Urals), Siberia north to lat. 57Â° in the Ob VaUey, Transbaikalia, the Amur and Ussuriland, south to Spain, northern Italy, Transcaspia, Turkestan and northern China. Migratory in the northern part of its range, wintering in southern Europe, northern Africa, Asia Minor, Syria, southwestern Asia, northern India, Burma, southern China and Japan.

value: Breeding visitor and Palearctic winter visitor, fields and mudflats: few breed Morocco; winters North Africa; vagrant Mauritania and in Sahara of Algeria, Libya.
Open fields, pastures, wet meadows, bogs, and grassy banks of ponds and lakes; in migration and winter also cultivated fields, seacoasts, and mudflats.
br.wide variety of open habitats w.short vegetation or bare ground, incl.wetlands, heaths, moors, arable fields, meadows, hay fields;non-breeding also in stubble & ploughed fields
